    <!--? @Cards @fullwidth  -->
    <h4>Fullwidth card</h4>
    <p>Used on <a tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/themes/air#section-publication">themecentre pages sections</a>,
      these cards are used to promote one featured content predominantly.
    <div data-xrayhtml class="prism">
      <div class="eea-card eea-card--fullwidth eea-card--landscape">
        <div class="eea-card-header">
          <div class="eea-card-title-wrapper">
            <div class="eea-card-title">
              <a tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/publications/europes-urban-air-quality" class="eea-card-link link-plain">
                <h2 class="notoc no-anchor">The way urban policies influence the air we breathe</h2>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="eea-card-body">
          <a tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/publications/europes-urban-air-quality" class="eea-card-image-link  link-plain eea-card-with-text">
            <img alt="" src="/publications/europes-urban-air-quality/image_large" class="skip_lazy eea-card-image  eea-card-image-bordered  eea-card-image--portrait" width="543" height="768">
          </a>
          <div class="eea-card-body-text eea-card-link">
            <p>Given their proximity to citizens and knowledge of local concerns, local authorities are best placed to ensure we make an effective transition to more liveable and breathable cities.</p>
            <p>Many city-specific measures have proved to be efficient but there is still much to do to empower citizens further and deliver coordinated actions across all governance levels.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="eea-card-footer">
          <a tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/publications/europes-urban-air-quality" class="moreLink link-plain">&nbsp;</a>
        </div>

